The log messages from compare are a known issue (see bug 172199) and have no impact on memory usage. Could you provide more details of your setup when the OOME occurred (How much memory are you giving to Eclipse? How many plug-ins in your workspace, etc)?

I have heap set to 256m max, and I generally have all of platform-ui and ui-examples checked out as well as my own skeletal scratch project and org.eclipse.osgi.  Nothing extraordinary.  I run with barebones SDK and the releng tools - nothing more.  The only unusual thing I can think of was having the unsaved compare editor open.

I've played around a bit and it does appear that the Update from the Sync View (at least, the model based sync view) does burn a fair bit of memory (especially when combined with the subsequent build on a big workspace). We haven't done any work in this area in 3.3 so this is not a problem that is new in 3.3. It would be worthwhile to investigate whether we can reduce the memory burn during 3.4.
Changing OS from Mac OS to Mac OS X as per bug 185991
